               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; a few lines alternating with black lines in the incipit page of Text I-1; headings and incipits of the texts, their sections and subsections; titles of the Biblical books and other works; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-8; directives for the ministers in Texts I-3, I-7 and I-8; the words ṣällǝyu in Text I-7 and nastäbäqwǝʿ in Text I-8; some interlineal corrections (e.g., fol. 78rc); elements of the punctuation signs, of Ethiopic numerals and of the text dividers.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- In Quires IV and V (Text I-6), some folios are misplaced; in the "Short content" (s. above), the right order is given.</note>
                     <note>- Fol. 39, loose leaf, is in reversed position.</note>
                     <note>- The text on fol. 41rv has not been identified.</note>
                     <note>- In many words, the 3rd order of a letter is written instead of the 5th; s., e.g., on fol. 53ra:</note>
                     <note>እግዚአብሒር for እግዚአብሔር (ls.6-7)</note>
                     <note>ኀቢየ for ኀቤየ (l.12)</note>
                     <note>በጊዚሃ for በጊዜሃ (l.18)</note>
                     <note>ይቢሎ for ይቤሎ (l.19);</note>
                     <note>on fol. 57r, the words:</note>
                     <note>ይቢሉ for ይቤሉ (fol. 57ra l.4)</note>
                     <note>ላዕሊክሙ for ላዕሌክሙ (fol. 57rc l.16).</note>
                     <note>- As nomina sacra, the name of Jesus is in this Ms. the name mostly rubricated. In the other Mss. with the same text, it is usually the name of Mary.</note>
                     <note>- The indications of the day and night hours are Usually not rubricated.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
